frameDefinitions: An Agent intends and takes steps towards bringing about a State_of_affairs or, metonymically, towards acquiring a Sought_entity .
A Cause triggers a System to operate in accordance with its intended purpose.
A Self_mover begins a journey at a Source location, in a particular Directiongenerally setting out with an Intended_goal in mind.
A Driver prepares a Vehicle for travel by placing it in the normal location for the operation of the vehicle or by detaching it from a place where it was held.
This frame describes either the creation of a Flame by a Kindler or non-sentient Cause, or the igniting of Flammables by a Kindler or a Cause.
An Agent acts to begin the life of a Process.
frameExamples: Smoking a cigarette will normally not <t>set off</t> a smoke alarm.
At about 1:00 in the morning, climbers <t>set out</t> for the summit.
Throughout Irish history, countless generations of exiles have <t>cast</t> <t>off</t> from the shores of Ireland.
Taliban militants recently <t>set fire</t> to several schools.
After discovering her knack for organization, she decided to try to  <t>launch</t> a career in human resources.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> makes an attempt to achieve a <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> or to  obtain a <fen>Sought_entity</fen>.
The entity that the <fen>Agent</fen> attempts to acquire.
A state or event that the <fen>Agent</fen> wants to bring about. The Agent may but need not be a participant in that <fen>State_of_affairs</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the attempt occurs.
The place where the <fen>Agent</fen> is seeking to achieve a particular <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> or to acquire a <fen>Sought_entity</fen>.
The <fen>Cause</fen> interacts with the <fen>System</fen> such that conditions are met for the <fen>System</fen> to operate.
The <fen>System</fen> interacts with or detects the <fen>Cause</fen> and activates.
An entity which participates in a <fen>Cause</fen>, perhaps volitionally and perhaps not.
The time when the triggering takes place.
Where the triggering takes place.
This is the entity which moves under its own power.

Any expression which implies a definite starting-point of motion expresses the frame element <fen>Source</fen>. In prepositional phrases, the prepositional object expresses the starting point of motion. In particles, the starting point of motion is understood from context.
The time at which the motion takes place.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the motion (which is specified by a <fen>Source</fen>, <fen>Path</fen> or <fen>Goal</fen>) is located.
This is the being, typically human, that prepares the <fen>Vehicle</fen> for motion, and will control it once it is in motion.
The device--such as a car, boat, spaceship,. etc.--which is used for transport and is prepared for travel by the <fen>Driver</fen>.
Any expression which describes the location that the <fen>Vehicle</fen> has been stationed at.
The  <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Driver</fen> prepares the <fen>Vehicle</fen> for motion.
The <fen>Place</fen> describes the location where the <fen>Driver</fen> prepares the <fen>Vehicle</fen> for motion.
The <fen>Kindler</fen> is the person performing the intentional act.
The <fen>Flame</fen> is what is created by the Kindler.
The Flamables is the the object that is set on fire by the Kindler.
The cause of the fire.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the event occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the event takes place.
This Frame Element marks expressions that indicate the process that the <fen>Agent</fen> initiates.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the actor responsible for starting the <fen>Process</fen>.
This role is for the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> initiates the <fen>Process</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Process</fen> is initiated.

<fex>His presence</fex> set off the motion alarms.
They let him through even though something triggered <fex>the metal detector</fex>?
<fex>She</fex> set off the silent alarm before being shoved into the middle of the lobby.
Three bombs were set off <fex>at three o'clock today</fex>.
Police came running downstairs when someone set off the metal detector <fex>at the county courthouse</fex>.
<fex>He</fex> shook his head in amazement and slowly pulled the car out of the parking lot.
Lyle was feeling very pleased with himself as he pulled <fex>the BMW</fex> out of its parking space.
We weighed anchor <fex>in the afternoon of October 9th</fex> and got out of the harbour under all plain sail.
At 0900 on 10 September 1945, DE 353 weighed anchor <fex>in Victoria Harbor</fex>, adjacent to Labuan Island, Borneo.
<fex>Mark</fex> started the fire with a magnifying glass.
